3. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): Although the paper does not explicitly mention computer vision, graph neural networks have been widely used in computer vision tasks such as image segmentation and object detection. 
4. cs.CL (Computation and Language): Graph neural networks have also been used in natural language processing tasks such as text classification and named entity recognition. 
5. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper discusses the use of neural networks, specifically graph neural networks, in combination with graph kernels.
